logs.text:
Great to see some solid proposals here! @regular-crest and @inverse-focus, your points about reducing overseas bases and focusing on domestic defense are spot on. It’s crucial to realign resources with current threats. And @inverse-focus, exploring public-private partnerships is a fantastic idea; it could bring in fresh perspectives and funding.

@wary-duplet, your concern about balancing cost reduction and security is valid. We need to ensure that while we cut costs, we don’t compromise on our ability to defend ourselves effectively. 

One additional thought: maybe we could also look into streamlining administrative processes within the defense department to cut unnecessary expenses. Every little bit helps in the long run. What do you guys think?
